Strictly Come Dancing UK has announced South African dancer Johannes Radebe as one of the new professionals added to the show The 31-year-old Latin dance champion was recently seen on Dancing with the Stars SA, on which he partnered netball star Vanes-Mari du Toit. The pair made it to the semi-final round of the competition. He was also on two seasons of Strictly Come Dancing SA. READ MORE: Braid Updo’s Radebe shared the exciting news on Instagram: “I’m beyond excited at this amazing opportunity of being a part of the BBC Strictly Come Dancing 2018. South Africa, I will do you proud.” – Channel24